  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor[Central/Cost Planning/main building tenders]",
  "description": "<p><strong>Duties &amp; Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepare quantity take-offs for tendering and cost estimation purposes</li>\n  <li>Source and obtain quotations for various trades, conduct price comparisons, and perform cost analysis</li>\n  <li>Identify and raise tender queries or discrepancies in design promptly for clarification</li>\n  <li>Manage tender correspondence and ensure all addenda and document revisions are updated accordingly</li>\n  <li>Assist in the preparation and compilation of tender submissions, including tender qualifications</li>\n  <li>Perform additional quantity surveying duties as required</li>\n</ul>\n<h5><strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong></h5>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or Degree in Quantity Surveying</li>\n  <li>1–3 years of relevant experience in main building construction tenders</li>\n  <li>Strong ability to read and interpret building drawings and specifications</li>\n  <li>Capable of working under pressure and meeting tight deadlines</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Microsoft Office applications</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with digital quantity surveying tools such as CostX or Glodon is a plus</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
